15:
And yet I sense that you still intend
to go...
29:
Sorry, Nao. I still have things to take
care of.
31:
I'll be back. You don't need to come
get me this time. 
...Though I'm sure it's hard to trust
me when I say stuff like that.
37:
For good reason! You had me
waiting for three whole months,
y'know?!
40:
That settles it. You'd better not keep
the young lady waiting again.
45:
Let's add some stakes here, Alk—if
you're late, she gets to boss you
around for a whole day.
50:
My goodness, Marina. That's quite
the heavy punishment.
58:
You don't have forever, y'know. This
place is coming down eventually.
You'd better come back before then.
67:
That's your uncle's blade. Use it to
get everyone out of here, okay?
76:
Thank you, everyone. Really.
I promise I'll be back!
80:
Marina... Where did Alk go off to,
exactly?
84:
To have a chat with a long-lost
friend.
89:
Come on, Nova. We'll wait for him
here.
109:
Mikoto! That's your name! Mi! Ko! To!
It means "life."
111:
...I'm your mother. Your Mama.
Ma-ma. Can you say "ma-ma?"
115:
It'd be nice to have someone to talk
to... other than myself...
121:
Mama! Yes, that's right! I'm your
Mama!
126: It's okay. I will... help... you, Mama.
128:
...What's wrong? It's me. Mikoto.
Don't be... afraid.
136:
You needn't feel sorrow. You have
brought us the child of God.
140:
Why, yes! His clairvoyance reaches
every corner of the earth—he
possesses the power to read the
hearts of all. Master Mikoto will save
the world!
142:
All of our hardships have been for
this very purpose! I'm sure it was
difficult for you, of course... Don't
worry, my child. You'll be well
rewarded.
146:
Indeed. Master Mikoto deserves a
life far away from the vile sinners of
the world. Just leave everything to
us.
148:
You should have nothing to fear. You
will be saved.
152:
I'm certain. There is no future for the
Starsayers—it seems they've made
too much of a commotion. They've
become too conspicuous.
154:
I'm already searching for a new
patron to fund my research. You two
should cut your ties with the
Starsayers as well.
156:
But... the clergy have taken such
good care of—
158:
You don't understand. It's not just
Mikoto. I need you, too...
164:
The time for prayer has begun.
Everyone is waiting.
167:
Ah, thank you for telling us. I look
forward to the results of today's
experiment, Mikoto.
173:
O-oh, just fine... Thank you for your
generosity, Master Mikoto...
182: The professor has turned against us.
184:
There's no mistake. I saw what was
in his heart.
187:
What do you mean, Mikoto? He's
been nothing but—
190:
Want to know what he said about
you? What he called you?
199:
Why did it have to turn out like this?
Why?
209:
Show me a world where my mother
can be happy.
212: A world in which I was never born!
235: I came here... to see you.
